text: Vaduz (German: [faˈdʊt͡s] or [faˈduːt͡s]; Regional dialect: [faˈdot͡s]) is the capital of the country of Liechtenstein. It has a population of about 7,500 people. Historically, Vaduz was the capital of the County of Vaduz, a state of the Holy Roman Empire. == Landmarks == * Vaduz Castle, the official residence of Hans-Adam II, Prince of Liechtenstein * Cathedral of St. Florin, cathedral of the Archdiocese of Vaduz, which includes the entire country of Liechtensten * National Art Gallery * National Museum
title: Vaduz
